<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="#990000"
    android:orientation="vertical"
    tools:context=".introduction">
    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent">

        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="match_parent"
            android:layout_marginLeft="10dp"
            android:layout_marginRight="10dp"
            android:background="#ffffff"
            android:orientation="vertical">

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="15dp"
                android:text="PRINCIPLES OF POSITIVE THINKING"
                android:textAlignment="center"
                android:textAllCaps="true"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="30sp"
                android:textStyle="bold" />

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="15dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Psychologically and scientifically, there is a huge amount of proof that our mentality and contemplations specifically impact our lives.
A simple case of this is it has been demonstrated that the straightforward demonstration of grinning really discharges the synapses dopamine, endorphins, and serotonin in your cerebrum, which make you more joyful.
Much like yawns, grins are additionally infectious."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Smiling can likewise enable ward to off worry, as it discharges certain neuropeptides that can help diminish pressure. Studies have demonstrated that discovering approaches to change your perspective of a distressing circumstance will enable you to oversee it.
This principle reminds us that, when we feel positive, we are more likely to act positively and over time create a life of greater well-being. Being able to experience positive emotions is a foundation to strengthen a sense of well-being, caring relationships, and increased energy and vitality.
Both negative and positive emotions create physiological, cognitive, and behavioral shifts. When people feel positive emotions, there is an “opening up” versus a “shutting down” effect. The “broadening” effect describes the cognitive, emotional, and physiological changes we experience when positive emotions are aroused."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Psychology today says,"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="&quot;Studies show that helping people see certain experiences — such as final exams — as demanding rather than dire, protects them from the negative effects of stress while delivering its positive effects, especially focused attention and speedier information processing. Changing the stress mindset not only minimizes the effects of stress, studies show, it enhances performance and productivity&quot;"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="But then there is effective thinking, this is the main priority of the successful, the way they think differs from others."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="This is a quote from the first book i read,"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:textStyle="italic"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="&quot;The person who knows how will always have a job, but the person who knows why will always be his boss.&quot;-John C. Maxwell."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:textStyle="normal"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="If you can change the way you think, you can change your life. Good thinkers rarely find themselves being victimized by the world’s dictators and connivers,they know what they think and are confident."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="How do you think? How do the people you lead think? It stands to reason that right thinking models right thinking, so as you lead, your followers will learn how to think by watching how you think, and your organization will adopt that culture."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="7dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="CONSIDERATIONS:"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="1. Changing your thinking will not be automatic."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="2. It will not be easy."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="3. It will be worth the investment."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="It is never easy to change things about a person or yourself,but it is a gradual process."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="7dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="HOW TO THINK POSITIVELY:"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="1. Expose yourself to good input"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="2. Expose yourself to good thinkers"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="3. Choose to think good thoughts"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="4. Act on your good thoughts"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="4dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="5. Allow your emotions to create another good thought"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="You can give through online charities, fund raisers to support youths and many more."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="6. Repeat the process"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Solomon pointed out many centuries ago that “There is nothing new under the sun,” so don’t enter into this thinking you have heard it all before. Consider the possibility that there are new and profound ideas waiting for you that have been “hidden in plain view.” I certainly learned myself and committed to do more of this thinking intentionally in the future. It will only make me more successful."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp"/>
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="There are many ways to think and most of us practice them from time to time. At the same time, we tend not to be intentional about the ways we think"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="John Maxwell “unpacks” thinking for us and helps us to see the many elements successful people use to live their lives. These 11 make up most of these behaviors of successful leaders and help us to see with a right perspective or paradigm:"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="4dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="1. Big Picture Thinking:"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Most leaders are big picture thinkers;"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="4dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="They see the vision before others"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="They size up situations and variables"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="They sense where the team is going"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Connect the past and the future"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Seize the moment"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="It keeps you &quot;in the right forest.&quot; You see as others see. It leads to team thinking. It expands your horizons. Learn continually by visiting new places, reading new books, meeting new people, learning new skills."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Become a listener. Try to get &quot;outside yourself.&quot; Take in other people’s thinking. Look for opportunities to learn"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="4dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="2. Focused Thinking"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Set aside time to focus. Focused thinking removes distractions. It clarifies the target. It gets you through this milestone and to the next step. Be selective and choose your priorities (Top Five, High Five). Do personality profile assessments and reflect on past successes. Focus on your strengths. 80/20…what brings the highest return?"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="4dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="You have to “Give up to Go up,” meaning you have to release some things in order to grasp others. You can’t know everything, pursue everything, or travel everywhere…in fact about 90% of what we will learn and know cannot be acted upon, so we have to focus. Releasing the incidental or urgent for what is important is not an easy lesson to implement."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="3. Creative Thinking"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="4dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="“Creativity is being able to see what everybody else is has seen and think what nobody else has thought in order to do what nobody else has done.”"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Creativity is the most valuable resource you bring to your organization. Few people figure out how to use this principle in abundance. Often, creative thinking is really dot connecting using a lot of previous learning. But you will not be able to create or connect those dots if you don’t understand the value of the thoughts."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="4dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Einstein held that “Imagination is more important than intelligence.” By keeping your options open for other ideas, you find the key to getting the best solution…not the only answer. There is a correlation between creative thinking and screwball thinking…suffer the screwball and his ideas. To foster creativity, tolerate a little oddness. Creativity is intelligence having fun."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="“Creativity is especially expressed in the ability to make connections, to make associations, to turn things around and express them in a new way.” Tim Hansen. Creative thinkers are fearless. You don’t use up creativity…the more you use, the more you gain."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Eliminate thinking that kills creativity:"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="4dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="I’m not a creative person"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Follow the rules"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Don’t ask questions"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Don’t be different"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Stay within the lines"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="There is only one way to do it"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Don’t be foolish"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Failure is final"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="We don’t have the time"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="We can’t afford a mistake"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="We tried that before"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Create an environment that encourages creativity. Avoid “The Box”"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="A Closing thought: As a man thinketh in his heart, so is he. Proverbs 23:7 It is imperative to gain a handle on how you think. But even though Solomon instructs us soberly, we still spend too little time nurturing and developing our ability to think, and think successfully. The last phrase in the book is taken from Philippians 4:8, one of my favorite verses ever."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="3dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Paul encourages us to think differently:"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="2dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="“Whatever things are true, whatever things are noble, whatever things are just…pure…lovely, and are of good report. If there is any virtue and if there is anything praiseworthy; think on these things.” You’re gonna like the way you think."
